                    <head>Officium visitationis per Episcopum</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false">
                                <p>Modern cardboard covers. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: Upper left corner, in pencil by a modern hand: <quote>A 132</quote>. In black ink by a modern hand: <quote>Officium Visitationis per Episcopum 1480. (Utskrift för Strengnäs stift?)</quote>. <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>: National Library book label with current signum.</p>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                </origPlace>
                                <origDate notBefore="1476" notAfter="1500">15th century, last quarter</origDate>
                            </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. The diocese of Strängnäs is mentioned in a later addition, but not mentioned in the text proper.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The fragment belonged to <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100536">Nils Reinhold Brocman</persName> (1731–1770), librarian at the <orgName>Royal Library</orgName> and antiquarian at the <orgName>Antiquities Archive</orgName> (see addition on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>). Brocman bequeathed his manuscripts to the Antiquities Archive in <date when="1770"/> (see transcription of his will in U 89). The fragment is not mentioned in the list of books, and has at some point probably been removed from either a manuscript or a printed volume.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>From the <orgName>Antiquities Archive</orgName> to the <orgName>Royal Library</orgName>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
